{"id": "duc04-testb-26:1#4", "contents": "The issue of continuing prosecutions is significant, with many believing that prolonged criminal reckonings of the apartheid era's horrors will only prolong bitterness and delay reconciliation. However, supporters of prosecution argue that denying justice to victims is a worse evil. The prosecutions could also have an impact on national elections next year, when the African National Congress will seek to consolidate its hold on power. The Truth and Reconciliation Commission's chairman, Archbishop Desmond Tutu, has called for a two-year time limit on prosecutions, but d'Oliveira has deemed this period \"wholly impractical.\""}
